* Status flags
*
* #TABLE(default, default)
* { =h Bit | =h Purpose }
* { $00 | Set during warp }
* { $01 | Set when all waves are completed }
* { $02 | Set when you die }
* { $03 | Set during chance stage }
* { $04 | Set during stage init }
* { $05 | Set for two-player game when one is game over }
* { $06 | Set during main loop }
* { $07 | Two-player game }
* TABLE#
status_flags:                          ; >71eb
       byte >00

* Stars move countdown
stars_countdown:                       ; >71ec
       byte >00

* Unused byte at 71ED
       byte >00

* Sprite countdown
*
* Decremented when #R$85E6 is called, and it reset to first byte of level data
* by #R$8A53. 4 sprite handler actions are only executed when counter is zero.
sprite_countdown:                      ; >71ee
       byte >00

* Countdown to enemy shooting
*
* Reset to 2nd byte of stage data. See #R$8541.
countdown_at_shoot:                    ; >71ef
       byte >00

* Time to next wave
*
* Reset to 6th byte of stage data. See #R$8541.
countdown_to_wave:                     ; >71f0
       byte >00

* Current player (0 or 1)
current_player:                        ; >71f1
       byte >00

* Frame counter
frame_counter:                         ; >71f2
       byte >00

* Score player 1
